review_blob: Outstanding appearance.. medium brown w/ slight red tint.. awesome, foamy head. Aroma is pretty tame.. spices, caramel, hops. Very creamy and smooth.. Alcohol non-existent.. get some caramel, banana, spices, hops on the taste. Not the greatest taste, but a very good beer.
Smell of malty, citrus, dark fruit and hops. Taste is spicy, Belgian yeast, malt.. some hops, maybe licorice. Its good.
Reminds of a stronger Witbier, maybe a Hoegaarden Plus. Great mouthfeel, its a good beer.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #6 - Seven Kingdoms

review_blob: Great floral hoppy aroma. Decent appearance. Taste is light hops, fruit, not bad.

Dark black appearance with small tan head. Smell is great. Outstanding, complex aroma.. rye, chocolate, malt, coffee, vanilla.. wow. A ton of chocolate in the taste... very little rye. It is a bit fizzy.. Excellent beer.
Nothing remarkable about this one.. A basic ale where the alcohol is somewhat present. OK.
Not a great beer... tastes like a beer that wants an IPA, but just didnt quite get there with the citrus or hops.
Nice reddish brown appearance. Smells like malty swill... decent taste, slight malt, goes down somewhat bitter and abrasive. Not bad.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Victory Beer Camp Alt Route

review_blob: Thin palate very light stout that is somewhat reminiscent of a brown ale. A bit strange mouth feel. Its ok

Your typical ale appearance. Smell is good, balanced, more malt than an IPA, more hop than your normal amber ale. Taste isnt tame like your typical Amber.. like a hybrid of a brown/old ale and IPA. Not bad.
Great looking Amber... golden yellow/brown with solid foamy head. Spicy sweet aroma. Complex taste.. spices, malt.. dry.. not a whole lot of hops. Its decent, very drinkable.
Great looking beer.. was a bit underwhelmed, given all the great reviews. Didnt seem that creamy or shake-like.. just a thin porter with some bitter dark chocolate notes.
Orangey golden brown appearance, with thick fizzy head. Good looking beer. Mellow aroma of tropical fruit, malt, hops. Taste of definite tropical fruit, malty hops.
UPDATED: APR 10, 2016

Smells great.. hops, sweet malt, a tiny bit of citrus. Looks awesome, heavenly golden brownish glow, with some haze and decent foamy head. Taste is balanced, not very bitter or crisp of a bite... citrus, hops.... This is an awesome beer.
Can taste the alcohol in this one... aroma of a standard porter, smooth.. Not the greatest, but solid.
beer_name: Long Trail Culmination Ale Imperial Chocolate Porter

review_blob: Hazy golden yellow color, decent foamy head. Great clean hoppy taste. Very balanced.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Calling IPA

review_blob: Very dark, slight red hue.. foaming head. Smell of malt, slight metallic notes with chocolate. Taste is solid, chocolate malts, creaminess.. a little bitter, a bit thin. Its a very good brown ale.
Above average appearance. Taste of typical pumpkin beer, with a bit extra spices. Very smooth.
Super smooth, dead aftertaste... tastes like coffee, sorta flat. Its good.
Blackberry on the aroma and taste... comes off sorta funky. Average appearance. Its just OK.
beer_name: Green Flash Pacific Gem Single Hop Pale Ale

review_blob: Epic tangerine on aroma and taste. Hoppy, blue moon with three orange slices on steroids.
beer_name: Green Flash Tangerine Soul Style IPA

review_blob: Wheaty fruity mellow taste. Nice palate, very drinkable. Smell is weak but fragrant and good.
At this point of the tasting, all of the beers started to blend together. Nothing too distinctive about this beer, but OK.
beer_name: Flying Dog Brewhouse Rarities: Chipotle Dark Ale

review_blob: Almost like a milk chocolate stout with just a hint of Mexican spices thrown in there.
beer_name: Flying Dog Brewhouse Rarities: Mexican Hot Chocolate Stout

review_blob: At this point of the tasting, all of the beers started to blend together. A standard BPA.
beer_name: Flying Dog Belgian Style Pale Ale

review_blob: At this point of the tasting, all of the beers started to blend together. Though, I typically dont favor bocks very much -- I held this one in pretty high regard.
A very nice ale. This was one of the few highlights at a local Flying Dog tasting.
An above average pumpkin ale, though I thought it to be a bit on the sweet side.
beer_name: Flying Dog Wild Dog The Fear Imperial Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: A very solid, drinkable IPA. Nothing outstanding, but a winner (at the right price)
beer_name: Flying Dog Imperial IPA - HBC-291 Single Hop

review_blob: An impressive beer.. I didnt get much sweet, but it was very spicy, as advertised.
A truly excellent porter, probably one of the best Ive ever had. Super strong of barrel notes. Loved it.
beer_name: Flying Dog Wild Dog Barrel-Aged Gonzo

review_blob: A little disappointed with this one. Expected more mango AND more habanero..
beer_name: Flying Dog Fever Dream: Mango Habanero IPA

review_blob: Smelled like potpourri... outstanding overall, maybe not so for a beer. Didnt really get the Earl Gray, just a somewhat artificial bunch of spices.
beer_name: Flying Dog Brewhouse Rarities: Earl Grey Black Wheat

review_blob: Its not overly tart, but theres not much more to speak of except for the cherries. Its OK.
A Very refreshing beer.. strong of citrus and juniper on the taste. A little thin/fizzy. Nice one.
beer_name: Flying Dog Brewhouse Rarities: Juniper White IPA

review_blob: Smell was fantastic Taste starts out strong of coffee, but then gets very flat.. the aftertaste was almost non-existent.
beer_name: Flying Dog Brewhouse Rarities: Cold Press Coffee Porter

review_blob: Oranges were definitely present on the aroma. A nice addition to the overall taste, though nothing overly impressive about this one.
beer_name: Flying Dog Bloodline Blood Orange IPA

review_blob: Lifeless black appearance, with some head. Smell is of chocolate and milk. Smooth, a hint of bitter.. very strong of chocolate. Its very good, wish it was stronger.
Looks like lemonade... kind of smells like it as well. Taste of wheaty citrusy beer. Good.
Taste of buttery hoppy something. Its quite strange. dont know if I got a bad batch or what.
Nice copper red color, head is smallish. Aroma fairly neutral, roasted malt. Big hops on the taste, not that much malt. Its solid.
beer_name: Ballast Point Tongue Buckler Imperial Red Ale

review_blob: Smell is citrus and hops.. great, decent color but tons of floaties.. Taste is something tropical. Very smooth, not too bitter. Floaties are a bit of a turn off. but its a great beer.

Typical macro swill appearance with a small amount of head. Passable grainy aroma with a tiny bit of skunk. Reminds of a Miller Lite, with a little less carbonation and a little more body. Its really not bad.
Aroma of wheat, citrus and spice. Taste is above average. Mouthfeel is smooth, somewhat thick. Not bad.

Average appearance.. very bubbly, not much head to speak of. Aroma is very nice.. clean, floral, sweet hoppy aroma. Taste is clean, citrus floral hops.. a hint of sweet malt. Palate is above average for an IPA. Good quality IPA.

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Great golden color, very little head. Smell is decent.. I get hops, some citrus.. a bit of funk. Taste is great. Heavy on citrus and hops. Pretty smooth. I like it.
Typical IPA appearance. Smells of great citrus. Taste is a bit sour/bitter. Palate is bitter.
Aroma of smokey malt. Appearance is lifeless dar, with a bit of head. Taste is roasted malt. Smooth. Good.
Aroma of great citrus, rye. Mediocre appearance. Tastes great, very smooth. Good beer.
